{
  "stem": "25639.10",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I thought of that, long before she told me that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But you know, something sounds so ridiculous.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But nothing is absurd.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nothing is ridiculous in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean that is Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because it's so totally opposite of normal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's-- anything is possible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When they want to experiment with genetics, they wanted to produce twins and triplets in the experimental camp, so that 20 years from then, Hitler could have another army.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because his men were being killed on the Russian front.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So why?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What was the secret to having twins or triplets?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I think of how we can reproduce now.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He could create an army today, and they all could look like him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And with the computer age, if something like this happened, why, we are all in trouble.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We must always be careful when it comes to prejudice, racism, and discrimination.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We must stay away from it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We must treat every human being as human.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This must not happen anywhere.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then my turn came to come to the US.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I traveled to Goteborg and took the beautiful ship, [SWEDISH].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there on that ship, I learned what a grapefruit was and how you eat it, by watching others on the ship.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I never saw such a magnificent fruit before.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And even today, I have half a grapefruit, almost every day.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] These bring back pleasant memories.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Even oatmeal, which I had at least for four weeks if not six while I was in quarantine in Sweden.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They fed us oatmeal, until our stomachs could expand and get used to more and more foods.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But oatmeal was the staple food.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I love oatmeal.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
